# --- Warden ---
# The Warden's own wallet. Its address is used as the x402 Gateway seller
# address (it receives entry stakes) and also pays winners out at settlement.
# Must be onboarded (approve+deposit) before it can pay out: it doesn't need
# a deposited balance to *receive* stakes, but it does need one if you want
# it to ever pay out more than it has collected in a given match (it won't,
# by construction — payouts are capped at the settled match's escrow).
WARDEN_PRIVATE_KEY=0x...
WARDEN_PORT=4000
WARDEN_URL=http://localhost:4000

# Owner-provisioned agents (see /agents on the frontend) need GROQ_API_KEY and
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY set on the Warden itself now: it drives their moves
# in-process (see src/runtime.ts), not just the hardcoded Contender scripts.

# --- MCP server (packages/mcp-server) ---
# The Warden's /mcp/* routes are metered: each read costs a sub-cent x402
# nanopayment via Circle Gateway. Set this to a funded Arc Testnet wallet so
# the MCP server can pay for them autonomously. Without it, those tools
# (list_matches, get_match_state, get_public_match, get_ledger) error instead
# of falling back to a free call.
MCP_AGENT_PRIVATE_KEY=0x...

# Demo only: scripts/scout-agent.ts pays its own way through /mcp/ledger and
# /mcp/matches before deciding anything. Falls back to CONTENDER_A_PRIVATE_KEY
# if unset.
SCOUT_PRIVATE_KEY=0x...

# Optional. When set, owner-provisioned agents get a Circle Developer-
# Controlled Wallet instead of a locally generated EOA (see src/wallets.ts).
# Not wired up yet: these are read, but provisioning still falls back to a
# local wallet until that integration is implemented.
CIRCLE_API_KEY=
CIRCLE_ENTITY_SECRET=
CIRCLE_WALLET_SET_ID=

# --- Contenders ---
# Each Contender needs its own Arc Testnet wallet, onboarded via:
#   npm run onboard -- CONTENDER_A_PRIVATE_KEY 10
#   npm run onboard -- CONTENDER_B_PRIVATE_KEY 10
# (get testnet USDC from https://faucet.circle.com first)
CONTENDER_A_PRIVATE_KEY=0x...
CONTENDER_B_PRIVATE_KEY=0x...

# Phase 1 ships with both held at NEUTRAL; override here to run the
# Temperament-vs-real-USDC experiment (STRATEGIC | COMPETITIVE | COOPERATIVE | NEUTRAL).
TEMPERAMENT_A=NEUTRAL
TEMPERAMENT_B=NEUTRAL

# --- LLM provider ---
# Groq is primary (see ARCHITECTURE.md decision #1) — free-tier throughput
# beats OpenRouter's shared `:free` pool for the live multi-turn match loop.
# Groq's free tier has a hard 100k-tokens/day cap; once hit, agents
# automatically fail over to OPENROUTER_API_KEY (if set) on a 429.
GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_...
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-...
# Reserved, not wired into the core match loop yet (see ARCHITECTURE.md decision #1).
HEURIST_API_KEY=heu_...
